output.crosstab_text:
For first degree graduates of Physics and astronomy, one year after graduation, Professional, scientific and technical activities was the most common industry for White ethnicity graduates, Administrative and support service activities, Financial and insurance activities, Information and communication and Professional, scientific and technical activities were the most common industries for Black ethnicity graduates, Information and communication and Professional, scientific and technical activities were the most common industries for Asian ethnicity graduates, Information and communication was the most common industry for Mixed and Not known ethnicity graduates, and Not known was the most common industry for Other ethnicity graduates.

The industry with the largest range in median earnings was Financial and insurance activities where Asian ethnicity graduates had the highest median earnings (£41,400) and White ethnicity graduates had the lowest median earnings (£32,600). The group with the highest earnings was Asian ethnicity graduates who worked in the Financial and insurance activities industry (median earnings of £41,400).
output.crosstab_title: Industry of graduate employment for graduates of Physics and astronomy by ethnicity, one year after graduation, male and female first degree graduates from English HEIs, APs and FECs, 2019/20 tax year.
